The Alchemy Alliance Creates:

1) Age of Empires Intellectual property, taking the following forms:
- Random Map Scripts (.rms files)
- Random Map Compilation Files/Tools (.m & .ods)
- Component Specifications for Random Map (CHEM-CSRM-XX Files)
- General Specifications for Random Map (GSRM-XX Files)
- Method Specifications for How to Create Something (MTHD-XX Files)
- Tournament Handbooks (HDBK-XX Files)
- Charter (CH-XX Files, not just "paperwork", this is also a guide on good sportsmanship)

2) Age of Empires Content, which may include the following:
- Livestreams of 1v1s or TGs or Community games emulating the values of the Charter
- Tournaments &| Showmatches with Unique Settings/Environments for players to try out and enjoy
- Castings of above mentioned tournaments
- Discord conversations about the above mentioned, with exploration on how to push the boundaries of possibility.

The Alchemy Alliance does NOT:
- Enter competitions together, and is not a "clan" or "guild" in the context of competitive exclusivity (E. G. it is possible to be a member of a clan and the Alchemy Alliance simultaneously).
- Create build order guides or strategic best-practices for AOE2. There are a lot of other groups and pro-players who do a better job at this, although discussion about how to improve may be incidental.
